Emma Trott ( born 24 December 1989 ) is a retired English racing cyclist from Cheshunt , currently based in Christchurch , New Zealand .
She rode for the Dutch women 's professional team Dolmans - Boels from the 2012 to the 2014 season .
On 10 May 2014 , Trott announced she would retire from road racing after the final stage of the Friends Life Women ’s Tour the following day .
She became a personal trainer and cycling coach in New Zealand before returning to the UK to join the coaching team for British Cycling 's women 's academy programme from November 2018 .
She is the older sister of fellow cyclist and Olympic Gold medalist Laura Trott , and the long term partner of New Zealand road racing cyclist Linda Villumsen .
